verbose_text: In a comparison study with cyclosporine [XREF_BIBR], collutellin A inhibited CD4 + T cell activation of interleukin 2 (IL-2) production with an IC 50 of 167.3 +/- 0.38 nM, while cyclosporin A in the same test yielded a value of 61.8 nM.
